+# Dialog Provider System
+
+This directory contains a type-safe, registry-based dialog management system that eliminates the need for hardcoded imports and conditional rendering.
+
+## Overview
+
+The Dialog Provider system provides:
+- **No hardcoded imports**: Dialogs are registered dynamically via a registry
+- **Type safety**: TypeScript support for dialog keys and configurations
+- **Lazy loading**: Support for code-splitting dialog components
+- **Flexible**: Easy to add new dialogs without modifying the provider
+- **Backward compatible**: Existing code continues to work without changes
+
+## Architecture
+
+### Core Components
+
+1. **dialogRegistry.ts**: The dialog registry that stores component mappings
+2. **registerDialogs.ts**: Central registration file for all dialogs
+3. **DialogProvider.tsx**: The main provider that renders dialogs dynamically
+4. **dialogKeys.ts**: Type-safe constants for dialog keys
+
+### How It Works
+
+1. Dialog components are registered in `registerDialogs.ts`
+2. When a dialog is opened via `openDialog(key, config)`, the key is stored in state
+3. `DynamicDialogContent` looks up the component from the registry
+4. The component is rendered with the provided props
+
+## Usage
+
+### Opening a Dialog
+
+```typescript
+import { useDialog, DIALOG_KEYS } from '@/components/common/DialogProvider';
+
+function MyComponent() {
+  const { openDialog } = useDialog();
+
+  const handleClick = () => {
+    // Using type-safe constants
+    openDialog(DIALOG_KEYS.CREATE_USER, {
+      title: 'Create New User',
+      payload: {
+        // Your data here
+      },
+    });
+
+    // Or using string directly (backward compatible)
+    openDialog('CREATE_USER', {
+      title: 'Create New User',
+    });
+  };
+
+  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Open Dialog</button>;
+}
+```
+
+### Opening a Drawer
+
+```typescript
+import { useDialog, DRAWER_KEYS } from '@/components/common/DialogProvider';
+
+function MyComponent() {
+  const { openDrawer } = useDialog();
+
+  const handleClick = () => {
+    openDrawer(DRAWER_KEYS.EDIT_USER, {
+      title: 'Edit User',
+      payload: {
+        userId: '123',
+      },
+    });
+  };
+
+  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Open Drawer</button>;
+}
+```
+
+## Adding a New Dialog
+
+### Step 1: Create Your Dialog Component
+
+```typescript
+// MyNewDialog.tsx
+export interface MyNewDialogProps {
+  onSubmit?: (values: any) => void;
+  onCancel?: () => void;
+  // Your custom props
+  myCustomData?: string;
+}
+
+export default function MyNewDialog({
+  onSubmit,
+  onCancel,
+  myCustomData
+}: MyNewDialogProps) {
+  return (
+    <div>
+      {/* Your dialog content */}
+    </div>
+  );
+}
+```
+
+### Step 2: Register the Dialog
+
+Add your dialog to `registerDialogs.ts`:
+
+```typescript
+// For non-lazy loaded (smaller components)
+import MyNewDialog from '@/components/path/to/MyNewDialog';
+registerDialog('MY_NEW_DIALOG', { component: MyNewDialog });
+
+// For lazy loaded (larger components, better performance)
+registerLazyDialog('MY_NEW_DIALOG', () =>
+  import('@/components/path/to/MyNewDialog')
+);
+```
+
+### Step 3: Add Type-Safe Key (Optional but Recommended)
+
+Add your key to `dialogKeys.ts`:
+
+```typescript
+export const DIALOG_KEYS = {
+  // ... existing keys
+  MY_NEW_DIALOG: 'MY_NEW_DIALOG',
+} as const;
+```
+
+### Step 4: Use Your Dialog
+
+```typescript
+import { useDialog, DIALOG_KEYS } from '@/components/common/DialogProvider';
+
+function MyComponent() {
+  const { openDialog } = useDialog();
+
+  const handleClick = () => {
+    openDialog(DIALOG_KEYS.MY_NEW_DIALOG, {
+      title: 'My New Dialog',
+      payload: {
+        myCustomData: 'Hello!',
+      },
+    });
+  };
+
+  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Open My Dialog</button>;
+}
+```
+
+## Advanced Features
+
+### Lazy Loading
+
+Use `registerLazyDialog` for components that should be code-split:
+
+```typescript
+registerLazyDialog('LARGE_DIALOG', () =>
+  import('@/components/LargeDialog')
+);
+```
+
+### Custom Loading Component
+
+Provide a custom loading component for lazy-loaded dialogs:
+
+```typescript
+import MyLoadingSpinner from '@/components/MyLoadingSpinner';
+
+registerLazyDialog(
+  'LARGE_DIALOG',
+  () => import('@/components/LargeDialog'),
+  MyLoadingSpinner
+);
+```
+
+### Dynamic Registration
+
+Register dialogs at runtime (useful for plugins or dynamic features):
+
+```typescript
+import { registerDialog } from '@/components/common/DialogProvider';
+import MyPluginDialog from './MyPluginDialog';
+
+// Register anytime during app lifecycle
+registerDialog('PLUGIN_DIALOG', { component: MyPluginDialog });
+```
+
+### Unregistering Dialogs
+
+```typescript
+import { dialogRegistry } from '@/components/common/DialogProvider';
+
+// Unregister a specific dialog
+dialogRegistry.unregister('MY_DIALOG');
+
+// Check if registered
+if (dialogRegistry.has('MY_DIALOG')) {
+  // ...
+}
+
+// Get all registered keys
+const allKeys = dialogRegistry.getKeys();
+```
+
+## Migration Guide
+
+The new system is **100% backward compatible**. Existing code using string keys will continue to work:
+
+```typescript
+// Old code - still works!
+openDialog('CREATE_USER', { title: 'Create User' });
+
+// New code - type-safe
+openDialog(DIALOG_KEYS.CREATE_USER, { title: 'Create User' });
+```
+
+To migrate gradually:
+1. Replace string literals with constants from `DIALOG_KEYS`/`DRAWER_KEYS`
+2. Enjoy improved autocomplete and compile-time checking
+3. No runtime changes needed!
+
+## Benefits
+
+### Before (Old System)
+
+```typescript
+// DialogProvider.tsx - Required hardcoded imports
+import CreateUserForm from '@/components/users/CreateUserForm';
+import EditUserForm from '@/components/users/EditUserForm';
+// ... 20+ more imports
+
+// Required manual conditional rendering
+{activeDialogType === 'CREATE_USER' && (
+  <CreateUserForm {...sharedDialogProps} />
+)}
+{activeDialogType === 'EDIT_USER' && (
+  <EditUserForm {...sharedDialogProps} />
+)}
+// ... 20+ more conditions
+```
+
+### After (New System)
+
+```typescript
+// registerDialogs.ts - Clean registration
+registerDialog('CREATE_USER', { component: CreateUserForm });
+registerLazyDialog('EDIT_USER', () => import('@/components/users/EditUserForm'));
+
+// DialogProvider.tsx - Dynamic rendering
+<DynamicDialogContent
+  dialogKey={activeDialogKey}
+  props={sharedDialogProps}
+/>
+```
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+### Dialog Not Found Error
+
+If you see "Dialog component not found" error:
+1. Ensure the dialog is registered in `registerDialogs.ts`
+2. Check that the key matches exactly (case-sensitive)
+3. Verify the import path is correct
+
+### TypeScript Errors
+
+If TypeScript complains about dialog keys:
+1. Add your key to `dialogKeys.ts`
+2. Ensure `registerDialogs.ts` is imported (happens automatically via index.ts)
+3. Restart your TypeScript server
+
+### Lazy Loading Issues
+
+If lazy-loaded dialogs don't render:
+1. Check browser console for import errors
+2. Verify the import path is correct
+3. Ensure the component has a default export
